s that the three authors’ texts analytically revolve around the irrational and affective aspect of heroization. They thereby create literary representations of how the heroic emerges out of the collective imaginary.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aGerman dramay18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPolitical plays, Germany18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 4aDrama (um 1800). 4aHeld/i.d. Literatur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aHeroes (in literature).08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2020z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831106580260 cprintz978311065385440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311066072240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110660722423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110660722.jpg  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Ebook Package 2020b2020  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DKUb2020